--API
-Application Programming Interface
-middleman
- It is an interface b/w two sets  of machines/stystem that allow you to communicate with another system/machine
api is like a waiter in a restaurant
you(client) -> give order(request)-> waiter(API)-takes order-> kitchen(server)- prepare food-> waiter-bring back the food

-GoogleMap API, weather api, payment api(stripe, razorpay), ai apis

Categories of API
-Public API-> available to everyone, weather api, maps api
-private API-> used within the organization. bank internal api, company microservice
-Partner API-> shared with selected partners only. Payment gateways
-Composite API-> combines multiple APIs in one call

Type API
-Soap-- Simple Object Access protocol, XML based(req, res), heavy, slower, legacy
-Rest-- Representational state transfer, uses HTTP, lightweight, JSON/XML
-GraphQL-> client decides what data it wants, by facebook
-grpc

HTTP -> hyper text transfer protocol
rest methods -> GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
rest should have
1.Uniform interface
2.Client-server model
3.Stateless(server not aware of state of client vice-versa)
4.Cacheble
5.Layered system

Request -> url, header, method, body
-base url
-endpoint
query parameter
-path parameter


Response-> status code, body, header,
200-successfull
201- created
fakestoreapi
openweatherapi
reqres.in


Testing the APis -> postman, bruno, swagger(documentation of apis)

